---
description: Review, queue, and safely land pull requests when a PR is ready or the user says deploy
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `.mergequeue.toml` and use the `deploybot` MCP tools. Keep changing
PRs draft and make the final ready head immutable. Address valid feedback from
whatever review providers the repository configures.

Only the user's exact `deploy` instruction authorizes enqueueing the current
thread's PR. The queue label wakes GitHub immediately; never poll or merge an
unlabeled PR. Merge independent ready work in order, skip blockers, honor
dependencies, and route overlapping source through one integration PR.
